==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Soundness
<hw>Sound"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or state of being
sound; <as>as, the <ex>soundness</ex> of timber, of fruit, of the teeth,
etc.; the <ex>soundness</ex> of reasoning or argument;
<ex>soundness</ex> of faith.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Firmness; strength; solidity; healthiness; truth;
rectitude.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Soune</ent>⟦br⟧
